 for bestpractices and # Admin Tools & Analytics

## Overview
Develop a comprehensive Admin Tools & Analytics suite for RepoMarket that enables secure admin-only monitoring, user management, system health insight, and operational controls. This includes dashboards and pages to observe analytics derived from Supabase metrics/logs, manage users (search, connect repos, purge data, adjust plans/credits), and execute admin operations such as queue/job retries and API key usage auditing. All endpoints and UI must enforce RBAC with Supabase policies, log admin actions immutably, and guard against null/undefined values in runtime code. The project should remain lean, with Supabase handling authentication, database, and storage, and integrations with GitHub, Anthropic, and Perplexity as described.

Associated Pages:
- page_admin_017
- page_admin_018

Target stack notes:
- Frontend: React (with hooks), TypeScript, likely Next.js or a similar framework. Use useState/useEffect patterns with robust null checks.
- Backend: Supabase (Postgres) for auth, policies, and storage; REST/Edge API routes or RPCs for admin operations.
- Integrations: GitHub for repo ingestion, Anthropic for repository context interpretation, Perplexity for external market data gathering.
- Data: Structured audit log of admin actions; metrics/logs derived from Supabase.

---

## Components to Build
1. Admin Dashboard (Internal Admin Console)
   - Overview widgets: system health (uptime, queue length, error rate), usage metrics (API calls, active users, plan distributions), recent admin actions.
   - Charts: compact, minimalistic charts with teal gradients (#2FD7BC → #14B9A0) and neutral axes (#D1D5DB).
   - Modals: confirm destructive actions (purge user data, force retry, disable API keys).
   - Cards: user management snippets, top API clients, recent audits.

2. Admin — User Management (page_admin_017)
   - Search and filter users (by email, id, plan, status, last active).
   - View connected repos per user; purge user data; adjust plan/credits.
   - Inline actions: edit user details, add credits, suspend/reactivate, assign roles.
   - Purge data flow: multi-step confirm with audit trail.
   - Data display: paginated table with robust guards for missing fields.

3. Admin Tools & Analytics (Core Admin Features)
   - Health monitoring: queue status, job retries, failed job counts, worker throughput.
   - Operational controls: queue/job retry, manual re-run triggers, pause/resume queues.
   - API keys usage: view, filter by key, usage counts, revoke keys, rotate keys.
   - Audit log: immutable trail of admin actions with timestamp, admin user, target entity, action type, and payload diff.

4. Admin Data Visualization Components
   - Compact charts and micro-visuals for metrics: bar charts, line trends, donut gauges for quotas.
   - Data source integration: consume from Supabase metrics/logs, with guards to handle null results.

5. Reusable UI Primitives (per design system)
   - Cards, grids, forms, inputs, selects, toggles, buttons (primary/secondary/ghost/teal accents).
   - Badges/pills (New, Warning, Inactive) with pale aqua backgrounds and teal text.
   - Tables with stable headers, sortable columns, and adjustable page sizes.
   - Confirmation modals and toast notifications for admin actions.

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages and routing
  - Admin Dashboard: route /admin/dashboard
  - Admin — User Management: route /admin/users (page_admin_017)
  - Admin Tools & Analytics: route /admin/tools (page_admin_018)
- State and data handling
  - Use React with TypeScript. Initialize all array state with proper defaults: useState<MyType[]>([]) for lists.
  - Guard all array operations: use (data ?? []) or Array.isArray checks before .map/.filter/.reduce/.find.
  - Safely handle API responses: ensure data structures are validated (Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []).
  - Deploy useEffect data fetches with cleanup, and provide loading/error states.
- UI Components
  - Cards with 14–18px radii, subtle borders (#E6E9EE), and drop shadows (0 6px 18px rgba(16,24,40,0.06)).
  - Top navigation: white bar with left logo, center muted nav links, right-aligned primary pill CTA (Login/Access Admin) depending on auth state.
  - Tables: sortable columns, pagination, accessible keyboard navigation, and safe rendering with null guards.
  - Forms: inputs with 8–10px border radius, 1px borders, focus ring in pale teal rgba(33,199,167,0.18).
  - Data viz: lightweight charts (bar/line) using pure CSS/SVG with teal gradient fills (#2FD7BC → #14B9A0) and subtle gridlines (#E6E9EE).
- Accessibility
  - ARIA labels for interactive elements, keyboard navigable modals, and proper color contrast (WCAG AA).
- Security & RBAC
  - All admin UI actions should require authenticated admin role; non-admins must be blocked at API layer using Supabase Row Level Security (RLS) policies.
  - API calls to admin routes must include role checks server-side.
- State defaults and null-safety
  - Default to arrays for list data: useState<Type[]>([]).
  - Always guard optional data: const items = Array.isArray(raw?.items) ? raw.items : [].
- Data integrity
  - Validate and sanitize all inputs, especially purge/delete actions and plan/credit adjustments.
- Performance
  - Debounced search for user lists; chunked/paginated fetches; lazy-loaded charts where appropriate.

### Backend
- APIs and endpoints
  - Admin authentication/authorization: ensure endpoints are accessible only to admin roles via Supabase policies.
  - User management endpoints:
    - GET /admin/users: fetch users with filters, page, pageSize.
    - POST /admin/users/:id/credits: add credits or adjust plan.
    - POST /admin/users/:id/purge: purge user data (with confirmation flow and immutable audit log).
    - GET /admin/users/:id/repos: fetch connected repos for a user.
  - System health endpoints:
    - GET /admin/health: system health metrics (queue lengths, worker status, error counts).
    - POST /admin/health/retry/:jobId: retry a failed job.
  - API keys usage:
    - GET /admin/apikeys: list keys with usage stats.
    - POST /admin/apikeys/:key/revoke: revoke a key.
    - POST /admin/apikeys/:key/rotate: rotate a key.
  - Audit log endpoints:
    - GET /admin/audit: query admin actions; immutable write-on-action.
- Data models
  - Users: id, email, status, plan, credits, connectedRepos, lastActive, isAdmin, createdAt, updatedAt.
  - Repos: id, userId, repoName, provider, connectionStatus, lastSynced.
  - Jobs: id, type, status, attempts, nextRunAt, payload.
  - APIKeys: keyId, keyValue (hashed in storage), usageCount, lastUsed, createdAt, revokedAt.
  - AuditLog: id, adminUserId, actionType, targetTable, targetId, payload, timestamp, ipAddress.
  - HealthMetrics: snapshotId, timestamp, queueLength, failedJobs, throughput, apiCalls.
  - Plans: id, name, price, credits, features.
- Data integrity & safety
  - Validate inputs; never trust client-provided data. Use RPCs with server-side validation.
  - Implement server-side guards to prevent mass purge or mass credit changes without explicit confirmation tokens.
- Supabase policies
  - Implement RLS to restrict admin endpoints to users with isAdmin flag, enforced on each query.
  - Audit log writes must be immutable by audit trail constraints; consider storing in a dedicated audit schema with append-only semantics.
- Logging
  - Every admin action must be written to AuditLog with timestamp, admin user, and payload.

### Integration
- Data flow
  - Admin UI panes fetch through Admin APIs; data must be validated and sanitized on both ends.
  - Admin Dashboard consumes system health metrics and usage analytics from Supabase; gracefully handle null results with empty datasets.
- External services
  - GitHub: for repo connections in user management; ensure OAUTH tokens are stored securely with rotation capability; log access events in audit.
  - Anthropic: for repository context analysis in other product flows; ensure safe handling of prompts and responses; logs included in audit.
  - Perplexity: used for external market data; protect API keys and error handling; results cached where possible.

