## User Experience Flow

1. Access and authentication
   - Admin user signs in via Supabase auth.
   - Frontend checks isAdmin flag and grants access to /admin/* routes.
   - If not admin, redirect to a safe page with an explanation.

2. Admin Dashboard access (Admin — Overview)
   - View health metrics: queue status, failed jobs, throughput.
   - See usage trends: API calls, active users, plan distributions.
   - Quick actions: retry a failed job, view audit logs, open admin tools.

3. Admin — User Management (page_admin_017)
   - Search input with debounce: search by email or user ID.
   - Results list with pagination; each user card shows plan, credits, lastActive, connectedRepos.
   - Actions per user:
     - View connected repos: expand to see repository list; fetch with guard against null.
     - Purge user data: initiate purge flow with confirmation modal; upon confirm, trigger server-side purge and write audit.
     - Adjust plan/credits: open modal to modify; validate delta; apply via API; reflect in UI.
     - Suspend/Activate: toggle status with confirmation.
   - Auditing: every action logged and visible in Admin Audit panel.

4. Admin Tools & Analytics (Internal console)
   - Health monitoring widgets with live-ish data or refreshable intervals.
   - Job queue controls:
     - Retry failed job: select job, trigger retry; confirm and log.
     - Manual re-run: trigger run and monitor status.
     - Pause/Resume queues: toggle global state; confirm.
   - API keys usage:
     - List keys with usage metrics; search filter; revoke/rotate keys.
   - Audit trail:
     - List recent admin actions; filter by actionType, date range; export option if required.

5. Data Visualization and Analytics
   - Dashboard charts present minimalistic visuals using teal gradient colors.
   - Ensure charts degrade gracefully if data is sparse or missing.

6. Accessibility and responsiveness
   - All components accessible, keyboard navigable, and mobile responsive with consistent spacing.

